Task Tracker CLI
A simple command-line interface (CLI) application to help you track and manage your tasks. The application allows you to:

Add, update, and delete tasks
Mark tasks as "in progress" or "done"
List tasks by different statuses (e.g., "todo", "in-progress", "done")
The tasks are stored in a local JSON file, ensuring persistence even after the program exits.

Features
Add a new task
Update an existing task
Delete a task
Mark a task as "in progress", "done", or "todo"
List tasks by status (all, done, in-progress, or todo)
Requirements
Python 3.x
No external libraries or frameworks (uses built-in Python modules)
Installation
Clone the repository:
bash
Copy
Edit
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/task-tracker-cli.git
cd task-tracker-cli
Ensure you have Python 3.x installed:
bash
Copy
Edit
python3 --version
If you are using a virtual environment, activate it now:
bash
Copy
Edit
# On MacOS/Linux
source venv/bin/activate

# On Windows
.\venv\Scripts\activate
Run the project using:
bash
Copy
Edit
python task_tracker.py
Usage
Add a task
To add a task, use the following command:

bash
Copy
Edit
python task_tracker.py add
You'll be prompted to enter a task description. Example:

arduino
Copy
Edit
Enter task description: Clean room
Task added successfully (ID: 1)
Update a task
To update a task, use the following command:

bash
Copy
Edit
python task_tracker.py update <task_id>
Example:

bash
Copy
Edit
python task_tracker.py update 1 "Clean room and organize closet"
Delete a task
To delete a task, use:

bash
Copy
Edit
python task_tracker.py delete <task_id>
Example:

bash
Copy
Edit
python task_tracker.py delete 1
Mark a task
To mark a task as "in progress", "done", or "todo", use the following commands:

bash
Copy
Edit
python task_tracker.py mark-in-progress <task_id>
python task_tracker.py mark-done <task_id>
python task_tracker.py mark-todo <task_id>
List tasks
To list all tasks:

bash
Copy
Edit
python task_tracker.py list
To list tasks by status (done, todo, or in-progress):

bash
Copy
Edit
python task_tracker.py list done
python task_tracker.py list todo
python task_tracker.py list in-progress
Task Properties
Each task has the following properties:

id: A unique identifier for the task
description: A short description of the task
status: The status of the task (todo, in-progress, done)
createdAt: The date and time when the task was created
updatedAt: The date and time when the task was last updated
Example Output
bash
Copy
Edit
$ python task_tracker.py add
Enter task description: Buy groceries
Task added successfully (ID: 1)

$ python task_tracker.py list
ID: 1, Description: Buy groceries, Status: todo, CreatedAt: 2025-02-01 12:30:00, UpdatedAt: 2025-02-01 12:30:00
